reviews.title: Formidable!
reviews.text:
Great food tonight.
Escargot- goat cheese tasting- meatball from our own kitchen and the vegetarian plate cake (super was this ). Good baguette with spreads beforehand!
Leffe Blond vd tap.
Nice wines by the glass.

Nice attentive service.
Always good with you.

-Thank you.

reviews.title: Delicious dinner with my wife
reviews.text: Great food and service. Top service. Very friendly. Food of all kinds. Venison steak melts on the tongue. Fish soup delicious.  Crepe to lick your fingers with, deliciously flambéed. Highly recommended.

reviews.title: Top experience, good food, good staff and nice French owners.
reviews.text:
Great food with two of us. Good and friendly service and a personal approach by the French owners. 

Both a different dish and different side dishes like a potato gratin, top!

reviews.title: Delicious casual lunch
reviews.text:
Nice place, nice property and we were lucky enough to have nice weather.
But the food is well prepared and will be on the table soon enough.
Staff is friendly and attentive so if you look around for 2 seconds you will be helped immediately.

reviews.title: Cozy and good
reviews.text: Very cordial on the phone. Very helpful, also regarding allergies. Felt safe in that regard. The food was tasty and again served in a friendly manner. Definitely recommended to come back when we are in Epe again. Many thanks to our “French waiter”

reviews.title: An asset to the catering square in Epe
reviews.text: I can be brief about the cozy atmosphere and service: great! But I think the fact that I ate a delicious grilled entrecôte there yesterday is special enough to mention here. The medium rare grilled sirloin of almost 3 ounces was of excellent quality and served plain with delicious side dishes. Highly recommended!

reviews.title: Disappointing experience
reviews.text: We came here after reading a rave review in the Stentor, but were disappointed. The food is o.k. but not special. However, what disappointed us most was the atmosphere. Apparently this is the meeting place on Saturday evenings for people in their sixties and seventies, mainly men, who become more and more vocal as time goes on. Eating a bite in peace is not an option. It's just a café where you can also have a bite to eat. Too bad, but perhaps our expectations were too high.

reviews.title: Great salad!
reviews.text:
We ate a delicious Posthoorn salad with you on Wednesday evening.
Good red house wine and friendly service.

Thank you !

reviews.title: Super bad; I will never come back here again; not even if I could have lunch there for free!!!
reviews.text:
For 12.75 euros I ate a tomato soup here that looked fresh but was stiff from salt; number 3. Indeed 2 slices of bread; and then really the simplest of the simplest (think of Aldi bread cheapest version)
A croquette okay here, little can go wrong and a very simple fried egg; and nothing more or less than an egg) As a garnish, 3 teaspoons of salad (more potatoes and mayonnaise than anything else) and a bowl of garlic sauce. What on earth would you do with this? Spread on the egg or croquette? or put it in soup?
Rarely had such a bad meal for 12.75 euros; really shame!!!!

reviews.title: Delicious steak
reviews.text: I visted the Posthoorn with my girlfriend over Easter while on a weekend break. The ambiance of the cafe is very inviting and the fact that it was full was a good indicator of good food. I had a steak with pepper sauce while my other half had the steak with a roquefort sauce.. Top class.

reviews.title: Good place to meet your friends
reviews.text:
My favorite place in Epe. Good croquettes, beer and wine, very friendly atmosphere.  

Good old friends meeting place for fun.

mgmtResponse.text:
Dear guest! 
Thank you for your kind words! We would be more than happy to have you with us soon again! 

Greetings from Epe,
Team Posthoorn

reviews.title: One of the best 'brown cafe's' in the Netherlands
reviews.text:
Once you are in Epe, you will have to visit 'De Posthoorn', right in the village center.
Watch the shopping people while sitting convenient on a causy terrace, enjoying your beer. Since this 'brown cafe' is regarded as the general livingroom for all locals and visitors: young or old, rich or poor, 'De Posthoorn' is the place you must have been. Well decorated, friendly and professional service, decent meals and all sorts of drinks.
I'm happy to recommend this to everyone.

reviews.title: food is really bad
reviews.text: food is just bad, because we have the feeling it isn't made with love. It is in a hurry.... The capaccio was too cold, the dressing of the salad tast dirty....And the people are working just for the money , no fun at all....

reviews.title: De Posthoorn
reviews.text: De Posthoorn is the place you should go if you want to have a drink and sit on a terrace in the middle of Epe. The two (male) waiters are very friendly.

reviews.title: My favorite
reviews.text: I live in Epe, and have tried most places,  but de Posthoorn stands out. It is THE archetype of a small town cafe restaurant. Brown inside, nice covered outside terrace. Decent menu, good prices, well made. Impeccable service, no students with an odd hour job, but real professionals who know what they do and with a tenure of a decade in the place. A must go to if you are in Epe.
